msgctxt "an3.96:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.96:0.2"
msgid "10. Loṇakapallavagga "
msgstr "10. A Lump of Salt "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.96:0.3"
msgid "96. Paṭhamaājānīyasutta "
msgstr "96. The Thoroughbred (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: bhadro → bhaddo (s1-3, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: saṅkhyaṃ → saṅkhaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.96:1.1"
msgid "“Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a fine royal thoroughbred with three factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and reckoned as a factor of kingship. "

msgctxt "an3.96:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.96:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, rañño bhadro assājānīyo vaṇṇasampanno ca hoti balasampanno ca javasampanno ca. "
msgstr "It’s when a fine royal thoroughbred is beautiful, strong, and fast. "

msgctxt "an3.96:1.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "A fine royal thoroughbred with these three factors is worthy of a king. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.96:1.5"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant with three factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world. "

msgctxt "an3.96:1.6"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.96:1.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno ca hoti balasampanno ca javasampanno ca. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is beautiful, strong, and fast. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.96:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant beautiful? "

msgctxt "an3.96:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. "

msgctxt "an3.96:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is beautiful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.96:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu balasampanno hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant strong? "

msgctxt "an3.96:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant lives with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They are strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities. "

msgctxt "an3.96:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu balasampanno hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is strong. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.245, sc4
msgctxt "an3.96:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu javasampanno hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant fast? "

msgctxt "an3.96:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … "

msgctxt "an3.96:4.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti; "
msgstr "‘This is the origin of suffering’ … "

msgctxt "an3.96:4.4"
msgid "‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti; "
msgstr "‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … "

msgctxt "an3.96:4.5"
msgid "‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’. "

msgctxt "an3.96:4.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu javasampanno hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is fast. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.96:4.7"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant with these three factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.96:4.8"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

